  "text": "Many of the Boolean networks from the literature are threshold networks [CITATION_1] . Each node can have a 0 or 1 value, and the value of a node when it is next updated is one if the sum of positive inputs minus the of negative inputs exceeds a constant threshold for that node. In analyzing and modifying these models, we found it to be necessary to extend threshold networks to handle more than two values.",
